Reasoning: The paper discusses the security of a compression and encryption scheme based on Chinese Remainder Theorem, which is a fundamental concept in number theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC) in analyzing the attack complexity. The scheme also involves system and control theory (cs.SY) in its design and implementation. Finally, the paper discusses some defects in the scheme, which could fall under software engineering (cs.SE).
